Students in Zhuhai, South China's Guangdong Province, receive nucleic acid test in April 2022. Photo: VCGGuangdong-Macao In-depth Cooperation Zone in Hengqin, an island located in Zhuhai in South China's Guangdong Province, announced on Monday that bus services and offline classes will be suspended from Monday for three days, as at least 34 COVID-19 positive cases were reported in Macao Special Administrative Region, which is adjacent to the zone.The suspension management started from 9 am Monday and will last for three days, with a mass nucleic acid testing conducted each day covering the whole zone. During the suspension, except for vehicles and personnel holding permits for epidemic prevention and control, emergency rescue, medical treatment and support, others can only enter the zone but are not allowed to leave. Online ride-hailing and bus services were also suspended.Kindergartens, primary and secondary schools within the zone have suspended offline classes and primary and secondary schools will carry out online studying, said the notice.In-house eating in restaurants and other entertaining venues have been suspended. Medical institutions, shopping malls and supermarkets to guarantee the normal operation of supplies will work normally and express delivery services will be available, according to the notice.Starting from Sunday, inbound personnel arriving in Zhuhai via Zhuhai-Macao ports (including Hengqin port) should show a negative result of nucleic acid test within 24 hours, Zhuhai authorities announced on Sunday.Macao special administrative region started a citywide nucleic acid testing on Sunday. As of 9 am on Monday, a total of 339,726 samples were collected, of which 198,301 samples tested negative. In addition, six samples (10 in 1 mixed sample) are preliminary positive, and re-checking has been conducted, according to the Macao SAR.Since June 15, individuals entering Zhuhai from Macao SAR shall report to their communities, employers or hotels immediately, undergo a 7-day home quarantine (without outside activities) and another 7-day self-health monitoring at home (not going out unless necessary), Zhuhai authorities said in a notice issued on Sunday. These personnel should not go back to workplaces, schools or visit public venues and avoid taking public transportation.Â Those entering Zhuhai from red-health-code or yellow-health-code zones of Macao SAR shall take 7-day centralized quarantine and receive a nucleic acid test each day, as well as another 7-day home health quarantine with nucleic acid testing required on the 10th and 14th day, according to Zhuhai authorities.A total of 13 people have received administrative detention for 10 days each as they didn't follow the related health management regulations and went to the public venues, causing the epidemic spreading risks after entering Zhuhai from Macao SAR, according to Zhuhai authorities on Monday.